other_tests.findings: Confirmed use of neurotic defenses to control anxiety; described as rigid and self-critical with intense dependency needs.
Noted extreme breathing difficulty, erratic breathing, anxiety, and inability to maintain normal activities.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Marked clinical improvement in breathing pattern, anxiety level, and general appearance observed after several sessions.

other_tests.findings: Initial concentration at 0.93 mEq/liter, later elevated to 1.08 mEq/liter during an acute episode.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Became 0.81 mEq/liter after discontinuing haloperidol and tapering lithium.

other_tests.procedure_name: WBC count and other laboratory tests
other_tests.findings: WBC count of 16,900 with 10% eosinophils; elevated alkaline phosphatase at 352 IU.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Returned to normal approximately 4 weeks after the toxic episode.
